{"name": "gitignorant", "metadata": {"name": "gitignorant", "version": "0.4.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A parser for gitignore files", "upload_time": 1730448855}, "documentation": ["# Gitignorant\n\nGitignorant is (aspires to be)\n\n* a [spec]-compliant .gitignore file parser and matcher\n* for Python 3.7 and newer\n* with full type hinting and test coverage\n* and nothing you don't need\n\n## Features\n\n* Parses .gitignore (and .gitignore style) files\n* Matches against list of parsed rules with the same\n  semantics as Git (\"last rule wins\")\n\n## Unfeatures\n\n* Trees of .gitignore files are not directly supported,\n  but can be supported by client code.\n\n[spec]: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore\n"], "modules": [{"name": "gitignorant", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "gitignorant.compile_pattern", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pat", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "re.Pattern", "xref": {"fqname": "re.Pattern", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gitignorant.try_parse_rule", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "line", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Rule", "xref": {"fqname": "gitignorant.Rule", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gitignorant._find_match", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rules", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Rule", "xref": {"fqname": "gitignorant.Rule", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "is_dir", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Internal helper function for check_match() and check_path_match().\n\nReturns True or False if the path matches any of the rules\n(where True is returned for positive rules and False for negative rules).\n\nReturns None if the path matches no rules."]}, {"name": "gitignorant.check_match", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rules", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Rule", "xref": {"fqname": "gitignorant.Rule", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "is_dir", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Check whether the given string (likely a path) matches any of the given rules,\nbut without any splitting of the path into components.\n\nSee check_path_match() for a version that splits the path into components."]}, {"name": "gitignorant.check_path_match", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rules", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Rule", "xref": {"fqname": "gitignorant.Rule", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "split_path", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Check whether the given path or its parent directories match any of the rules.\n\nIn other words,\n\n* Split the path into directory and the filename (using `split_path`)\n* Split the directory into directory parts (using `os.sep`)\n* For each directory part from left to right, merge it with all previous directory\n  parts and check that against all rules with `is_dir=True`\n    * If a positive match is found, return `True` immediately\n    * If no match or a negative match, keep iterating for a possible positive match\n      deeper in the path\n* If loop finishes, finally check exact path match with `is_dir=False`.\n  If no match, return `False`."]}, {"name": "gitignorant.parse_gitignore_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "TextIO", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TextIO", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Iterabl